"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49785","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-12","<p /> <p /> <p>These are two entirely different schemes and we would expect the requirements of placements for offenders to be very different. The welfare to work companies we have contracted to provide Community Work Placements are experienced at delivering different programmes across different areas of Government.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49785/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49785/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he has taken to ensure that unemployed people who volunteer for the Help to Work Scheme do not do the same work as offenders on community service orders.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","197780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49786","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-12","<p>No UK Minister was available to attend the World Economic Forum being held in Abuja on 7 – 9 May. We did propose to send senior officials, but the organisers of the World Economic Forum declined this request.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49786/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49786/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, who will represent the Government at the World Economic Forum on Africa in Abuja.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","197777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49787","Home Office","false","2014-05-13","<p> </p><p>It is not the policy of the Home Office to comment on the detail of individual <br>applications.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49787/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49787/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49787/answer/previousversion/9392","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the names are of all those issued visas in connection with the current visit of President Museveni of Uganda.","false","Biography information for Crispin Blunt","Reigate","Crispin Blunt","197911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49788","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-12","<p>This new polar flagship presents a significant opportunity for British business to show that they can compete with the best in the world. The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) will be working hard to make sure that British business are aware of the major opportunities around the project. The UK has world class skills and technology in this area and the Government hopes that UK marine and maritime companies will take the wider range of opportunities – from the design and building of the ship, through to its operation and maintenance.</p><p> </p><p>This ship will cost more than £200 million and legally it has to be procured through open competition. This ensures a fair process so that the UK gets the best possible product with the best value to the taxpayer. The Natural Environment Research Council's British Antarctic Survey will be operating the ship. They will be consulting the scientific community on the detailed specification for the ship shortly. An invitation to tender is expected to be issued in summer 2015.</p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49788/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49788/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the announcement of 25 April 2014, entitled Chancellor puts UK at forefront of ocean research with new polar science ship, if he will take steps to ensure that the new polar research ship is constructed in a UK shipyard.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","197970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49789","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-12","<p>The Office of the Deputy Prime Minster is an integral part of my department.</p><p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49789/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49789/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much was spent by the Office of the Deputy Prime Minister on tea and biscuits in (a) 2012-13 and (b) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","197980"
