tland, Wales and Northern Ireland, 2008-09 to 2012-13</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="5"><p>£</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"> </td><td><p><strong>2008-09</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009-10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>outturn</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>outturn</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>outturn</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>outturn</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>outturn</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scotland</p></td><td><p>119</p></td><td><p>117</p></td><td><p>117</p></td><td><p>119</p></td><td><p>119</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wales</p></td><td><p>113</p></td><td><p>112</p></td><td><p>113</p></td><td><p>116</p></td><td><p>114</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Northern Ireland</p></td><td><p>126</p></td><td><p>124</p></td><td><p>124</p></td><td><p>127</p></td><td><p>128</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: per capita expenditure data from Country and Regional Analyses 2013</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49929/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49929/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Deighton on 23 April (HL 6672), for each £100 of identifiable public expenditure per capita in England, for each of the last ten years, how much was spent in (1) Wales, (2) Scotland, and (3) Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Lord Selkirk of Douglas",,"Lord Selkirk of Douglas","HL6895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49930","Department for Education","false","2014-05-12","<p>When community schools convert to academies, the freehold is retained by the local authority and a lease is granted to the academy trust.</p><p>There are strict rules protecting publicly-funded land used by academies, regardless of who holds the freehold. This is set out in published guidance, which is available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-school-playing-fields-and-public-land-advice" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-school-playing-fields-and-public-land-advice</a></p><p>A copy of the guidance has been placed in the House Library.</p><p>The Department for Education does not hold information about the average value of land used for academies, or about the legal costs associated with establishing leasehold or freehold arrangements.</p><p>Academies are run by academy trusts, which are charities limited by guarantee – academies are not operated by private companies.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson","197851 ; 197853","2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49930/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49930/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average value is of the title deed of a local authority school that becomes an academy.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","197852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49931","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-14","<p>A list of members is available in the Library, and online at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>.</p><p>In line with the practice of previous governments, information relating to the proceedings of Cabinet Committees, including what issues were discussed, is generally not disclosed as to do so could harm the frankness and candour of internal discussion.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49931/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49931/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49931/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government who are the members of the Prime Minister's Growth Council; and how many times it has met since its creation.","false","Biography information for Lord Hennessy of Nympsfield",,"Lord Hennessy of Nympsfield","HL6896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49932","Department for Education","false","2014-05-12","<p>When community schools convert to academies, the freehold is retained by the local authority and a lease is granted to the academy trust.</p><p>There are strict rules protecting publicly-funded land used by academies, regardless of who holds the freehold. This is set out in published guidance, which is available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-school-playing-fields-and-public-land-advice" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-school-playing-fields-and-public-land-advice</a></p><p>A copy of the guidance has been placed in the House Library.</p><p>The Department for Education does not hold information about the average value of land used for academies, or about the legal costs associated with establishing leasehold or freehold arrangements.</p><p>Academies are run by academy trusts, which are charities limited by guarantee – academies are not operated by private companies.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson","197851 ; 197852","2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49932/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49932/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much his Department has paid in legal fees since 2010 on the transfer of title deeds of a local authority schools becoming academies.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","197853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49933","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-14","<p /> <p /> <p>Obtaining the information requested would involve the 35 probation trusts in searching the individual records of offenders and this could not be done without incurring disproportionate cost.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49933/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49933/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many repeat offenders serving prison sentences of less than one year have been provided with a resettlement package to facilitate their return to the community in the past year.","false","Biography information for Lord Ouseley",,"Lord Ouseley","HL6897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49934","Department for Education","false","2014-05-12","<p>When community schools convert to academies, the freehold is retained by the local authority and a lease is granted to the academy trust.</p><p>There are strict rules protecting publicly-funded land used by academies, regardless of who holds the freehold. This is set out in published guidance, which is available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-school-playing-fields-and-public-land-advice" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-school-playing-fields-and-public-land-advice</a></p><p>A copy of the guidance has been placed in the House Library.</p><p>The Department for Education does not hold information about the average value of land used for academies, or about the legal costs associated with establishing leasehold or freehold arrangements.</p><p>Academies are run by academy trusts, which are charities limited by guarantee – academies are not operated by private companies.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson","197852 ; 197853","2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49934/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49934/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many title deeds of local authority schools have been transferred to academies operated by private companies since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","197851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49935","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Under our Transforming Rehabilitation reforms the market will be opened up to a diverse range of new rehabilitation providers, so that we get the best out of the public, voluntary and private sectors, at the local as well as national level. Evidence from implementing our pilots and from the experience of other departments in using Payment by Results has informed the strategy, as has engagement with co-commissioning partners at a national, Police and Crime Commissioner and Local Authority level.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to assess impacts through a robust contract management system, only paying providers in full for real reductions in reoffending. We are on course to award and mobilise the new contracts for delivering rehabilitation services by 2015.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice does not hold data centrally on how may many repeat offenders are not receiving rehabilitation services prior to release from prison. However, as a result of our reforms, for the first time in recent history, statutory supervision and rehabilitation will be provided on release from custody to all 50,000 of those sentenced to less than twelve months in prison.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49935/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49935/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49935/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the effects and impact of the Transforming Rehabilitation Strategy 2013 to date; and how many repeat offenders are not in receipt of a facilitated resettlement programme to enable their return to the community when they leave prison.","false","Biography information for Lord Ouseley",,"Lord Ouseley","HL6898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49936","Department for Education","false","2014-05-12","<p>As of 1 May 2014, 3,688 local authority schools have become academies since 2010.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49936/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49936/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many local authority schools have become academies since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","197850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49937","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>The number of registered charities in England and Wales has increased slightly from 162,415 on 31 December 2010 to 164,158 on 31 March 2014. During the same period the annual gross income of registered charities rose significantly from £53.86 billion to £63.64 billion.</p><p>The Charity Commission removes around 6,000 charities from its register every year and registers a similar number.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49937/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49937/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49937/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the number of voluntary organisations undertaking charitable work activities that have ceased functioning since 2010; and what they consider to be the implications for meeting the social and support needs of vulnerable communities.","false","Biography information for Lord Ouseley",,"Lord Ouseley","HL6899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49938","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-12","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave the hon. Member for Hayes and Harlington on 24 March 2014 (Official Report) Column Ref: 65W.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49938/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49938/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49938/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which government departments offer payroll deduction for staff wishing to save with a credit union.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","197849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49940","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-12","<p>Details of external ministerial meetings are published at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications</a></p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49940/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49940/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49940/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many  times Ministers have met the Women's Business Council flexible working champion John Timpson in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","197741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49941","Home Office","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Home Office recognises the impact that exposure to domestic violence and abuse can have on children, as stated in the second national policy report, In plain sight: effective help for children exposed to domestic abuse (2014), produced by the Co-ordinated Action Against <br>Domestic Abuse.<br><br>The Government's approach to tackling domestic violence and abuse is laid out in the Violence Against Women and Girls Action Plan, refreshed in March 2014: <br><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/287758/VAWG_Action_Plan.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/287758/VAWG_Action_Plan.pdf</a> . <br><br>This sets out our commitment to work with the Troubled Families Programme, particularly identifying learning around intervening with families where domestic violence is an issue. We will be taking forward action to consider interim data from the independent evaluation of the Troubled <br>Families Programme to assess the prevalence of domestic violence within families currently being worked with and to inform practice in services for troubled families. <br><br>Domestic violence and abuse training for health visitors to provide support to families where they suspect violence against women or children may be a factor was developed in autumn 2013 and was rolled out this year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Taylor of Holbeach",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49941/answer","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49941/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49941/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their assessment of the Co-ordinated Action Against Domestic Abuse's Second National Policy Report, In plain sight: effective help for children exposed to domestic abuse, publishedin February 2014.","false","Biography information for Lord Laming",,"Lord Laming","HL6901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49942","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-08","<p /> <p /> <p>The information requested is routinely published and can be found at</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pre-work-programme-support-new-enterprise-allowance-march-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pre-work-programme-support-new-enterprise-allowance-march-2014</a></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49942/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49942/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of those benefiting from the new enterprise allowance are (a) women and (b) men aged (i) up to 24 and (ii) over 25.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","197756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49943","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-13","<p>The Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government did not grant permission for London Luton Airport's expansion plans, but did decide not to ‘call-in' the planning application. The determination of the planning application is a matter for the local planning authority, Luton Borough Council. This includes the consideration of any conditions that could be attached to a planning consent. I understand that the council has imposed planning conditions to mitigate the impacts of the development, including in relation to surface access, if permission is granted.</p><p> </p><p />",,"Baroness Kramer",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49943/answer","Biography information for Baroness Kramer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49943/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether, in granting permission for the Luton Airport expansion plans, they attached any conditions which would improve the current interchange arrangements at Luton Parkway station.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL6902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49944","Women and Equalities","false","2014-05-13","<p>The Women's Business Council has already met on two occasions this year to progress the recommendations in its report published in 2013: on 5 March 2014 and 24 April 2014.</p><p> </p><p>Women's Business Council members have met with Minsters four times during the last 12 months.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49944/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49944/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Ministers for Women and Equalities, how many times the Women's Business Council has met in 2014; and how many times Ministers met that council in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","197766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49945","Department for Education","false","2014-05-14","<p>Under the Control of Asbestos Regulations 2012, the employer - either the local authority or the school - has clear responsibilities to manage asbestos-containing materials in schools safely. We expect schools to have an asbestos management plan in place and to actively manage it in line with legal requirements.</p><p>The Department for Education takes the issue of asbestos management in schools seriously. Our policy, as in other aspects of school management, is to give schools the support that they need to fulfil their responsibilities effectively.</p><p>We have set up the Asbestos in Schools Steering Group to raise awareness and promote the effective management of asbestos in schools and published new guidance in October 2012 which is available on the gov.uk website:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/asbestos-management-in-schools" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/asbestos-management-in-schools</a></p><p>We also asked the Committee on Carcinogenicity (CoC) to review the relative vulnerability of children to low levels of asbestos exposure. We committed to review our asbestos policy following publication of the CoC statement and this review is currently underway.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49945/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49945/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking in relation to asbestos in schools.","false","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","HL6903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49946","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-12","<p /> <p /> <p>Statistics on the number of people aged 24 and under who have been referred to the Work Programme were identified as being from an ethnic minority background and (i) attached to a Work Programme provider, (ii) attained a job outcome and (iii) received at least one sustainment payment can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/WorkProg/tabtool.html" target="_blank">http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/WorkProg/tabtool.html</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance</a></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49946/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49946/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what information his Department holds on (a) the ethnicity of people aged 24 years and under referred to the work programme and (b) the number of those aged 24 years and under who have (i) been attached to a work service provider, (ii) attained a job outcome payment and (iii) received at least one sustainment payment.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","197768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49947","Department for Education","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Department for Education does not conduct air quality testing in schools. Under the Control of Asbestos Regulations 2012, the employer – either the local authority or the school – has clear responsibilities to manage asbestos-containing materials in schools safely. The regulations include a requirement that exposure to asbestos fibres is reduced to a level that is as low as reasonably practicable.</p><p>The condition of asbestos containing materials can be monitored by visual inspection and by checking for any signs of damage. In some cases the employer may arrange for air sampling to be done to establish the levels of asbestos fibres.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49947/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49947/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how they are testing air quality in schools.","false","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","HL6904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49948","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-13","<p /> <p /> <p>The analysis required to answer this question is not currently available. To answer this question requires analysis across a number of data sources to include all women and men of working age. If a robust outcome can be reached it will be published on the DWP website.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49948/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49948/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number and proportion of working age (a) men and (b) women who do not meet the wage criteria for eligibility for auto-enrolment; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","197764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49949","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-14","<p /> <p /> <p>Carefully managing prisoners into the community on temporary licence toward the end of their sentence is a key part of efforts to rehabilitate them back into society. Release on Temporary Licence (ROTL) plays an important role in public protection by ensuring that offenders are tested in the community under strict conditions before being released. It also provides a valuable means of helping prisoners prepare for their resettlement in the community by, for example, finding work or rebuilding links with their families, which helps to reduce reoffending.</p><p> </p><p>But this should never be at the expense of public safety which remains our absolute priority.</p><p> </p><p>In March this year, the Government announced plans to improve temporary release policy and practice following reviews prompted by three very serious incidents last year. A key part of these plans is to have a new scheme of restricted ROTL for serious offenders. In those cases, there will be more stringent risk assessment procedures, with greater involvement of psychology and probation professionals and more restrictive licence conditions. In addition, and as soon as suitable equipment is available, we will be able to tag offenders on temporary release.</p><p> </p><p>In the vast majority of cases ROTL is used effectively and successfully. Prisoners fail to comply with licence conditions in less than one tenth of one per cent of cases.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49949/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49949/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their policy on the release of prisoners on temporary licence.","false","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","HL6905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49950","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-13","<p /> <p /> <p>There are 230,000-260,000 female workers with multiple jobs who have total earnings above the automatic enrolment earnings trigger (£10,000 in 2014/15). Just 40,000-50,000 of these are ineligible for automatic enrollment because they earn less than the earnings trigger in any one of their jobs. A majority of these workers have earnings above the lower limit of the automatic enrolment qualifying earnings band (£5,772 in 2014/15) in at least one job and so can opt-in to a pension scheme with a mandatory contribution from their employer. Further detail is available in <em>Workplace Pension Reform: Multiple Jobholders</em>, DWP, available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/211729/ad-hoc-multiple-jobs.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/211729/ad-hoc-multiple-jobs.pdf</a></p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49950/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49950/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of women with multiple part-time jobs whose total earnings are above the threshold for automatic enrolment; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","197739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49951","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-13","<p>It is in the UK national interest that the Portuguese, and wider euro area, economy is successful and we welcome the Portuguese Government's strong commitment to its Economic Adjustment Programme, and the progress achieved under it. Treasury officials closely monitor developments in Portugal and the rest of the euro area, as with all major economies, as part of the normal policy development process.</p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49951/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49951/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the impact on the United Kingdom economy of Portugal's exit from the European Union financial assistance programme.","false","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","HL6906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49952","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-12","<p /> <p /> <p>In September 2013 we published the “Framework for the analysis of future pension incomes” which contained details of our modelling of adequate retirement incomes. Recognising that an individual's income in working life affects the retirement income that they would deem to be adequate, we use replacement rates (the ratio of retirement income to working age income) instead of a single income value to assess adequacy.</p><p> </p><p>We use the following set of five replacement rate targets as determined in the Pensions Commission's 2004 report to define adequate replacement rates:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Average annual equivalised gross household earnings between 50 and State Pension Age (2014 earnings terms)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Target replacement rate for adequate retirement income</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Under £12,300</p></td><td><p>80%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£12,300 to £22,700</p></td><td><p>70%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£22,700 to £32,500</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£32,500 to £52,000</p></td><td><p>60%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Over £52,000</p></td><td><p>50%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>To account for income sharing among couples, we use equivalised household level income for both working age and retirement incomes.</p><p> </p><p>Using the Department's Pensim2 model we look at the simulated replacement rates of individuals reaching State Pension age between 2014 and 2059, yielding around 27.9 million individuals in our adequacy measure.</p><p> </p><p>Our analysis shows that we expect there around 56 per cent (around 15.7 million) of those individuals to have an adequate replacement rate. It also shows that around a) 55 per cent of men and b) 57 per cent of women in our measure will have an adequate replacement rate.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49952/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49952/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49952/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent estimate he has made of what constitutes an adequate retirement income; what estimate he has made of the proportion of (a) men and (b) women who will achieve this income; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","197763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49953","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-14","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to this question in the time available before Prorogation. I will correspond directly with the noble Lord as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49953/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49953/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how they have promoted Fair Trade Day.","false","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","HL6907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49954","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-13","<p> </p><p>The UK regularly meets Palestinian Authority ministers, most recently on 6 March 2014 as part of our regular strategic dialogue to discuss progress against commitments in our Memorandum of Understanding. The discussion covered the range of areas of cooperation (including security and justice, finance and the economy) as well as progress on developing the new Palestinian National Development Plan.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49954/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49954/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent discussions she has had with the Palestinian Authority on that body's use of UK funding.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","197752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49955","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p>On 5 May 2014, the World Health Organisation (WHO) issued a statement regarding the recent international spread of wild poliovirus and Temporary Recommendations (TR) under the International Health Regulations 2005 to prevent its further spread. The TR are primarily focused on countries exporting and/ or infected with wild polio virus. The Government fully supports the WHO statement.<br> <br> The UK remains deeply committed to the eradication of polio, and is a long-time supporter of the Global Polio Eradication Initiative. At the Global Vaccine Summit in Abu Dhabi in 2013 DFID pledged up to £300 million for polio eradication. In 2013 DFID also provided additional support for the outbreaks in the Horn of Africa and Syria.</p>",,"Baroness Northover",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49955/answer","Biography information for Baroness Northover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49955/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to prevent the worldwide spread of polio.","false","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","HL6908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49956","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-12","<p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) first discussed climate change with the Australian Minister for Foreign Affairs at the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting in Sri Lanka last November, and more recently at their annual bilateral in March. In each conversation, it was agreed that securing a binding, global deal in 2015 was a shared aim and to explore ways to achieve that through partnership.</p><p>While the Foreign Secretary has yet to discuss specifically the latest report from the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, my right hon. Friend the Member for Kingston and Surbiton (Mr Davey) has discussed this with the Australian Environment Minister, and they agreed on the need for global action on climate change.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49956/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49956/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Australian counterpart on the report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change on Climate Impacts, Adaptation and Vulnerability; and what representations he has made to the Australian government in support of global co-operation to reduce emissions.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","197848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49957","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>Details of Ministerial meetings with external stakeholders are published quarterly in arrears on the Gov.uk website at:</p><p> </p><p>www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-2013#department-of-health-dh</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not keep a central diary of the engagements that every Departmental official has had with representatives of Action on Smoking and Health or other third party groups. In discharging their official duties, Ministers, special advisors and Departmental officials meet with representatives from such organisations in a wide range of fora, including speaking engagements, conferences and seminars.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has no plans to proactively publish briefings or other materials relevant to meetings about standardised packaging of tobacco products.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49957/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49957/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what meetings have taken place between Ministers or officials of the Department of Health with representatives of Action on Smoking and Health and other third party groups regarding the introduction of standardised tobacco packaging; and whether they will publish any briefing or material for each relevant meeting.","false","Biography information for Lord Palmer",,"Lord Palmer","HL6909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49958","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>Standardised packaging of tobacco products is a policy that is still under consideration by the Government. Therefore, no final decisions have been made regarding the policy. The Government will be publishing a final, short consultation that will contribute to final decision-making.</p><p> </p><p>The Department's policy development activity is undertaken in accordance with the Government's policy on better regulation.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49958/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49958/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the conformity of the introduction of standardised packaging for tobacco with the better regulation principles; and how they intend to review or assess the impact of such proposals.","false","Biography information for Lord Palmer",,"Lord Palmer","HL6910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49959","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Department published a consultation-stage impact assessment (IA) alongside the <em>Consultation on standardised packaging of tobacco products </em>in 2012 that covered potential costs and benefits. The consultation asked 12 questions that were specific to this IA.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will hold a final, short consultation on standardised packaging of tobacco products. In this consultation Ministers will ask, in particular, for views on anything new since the last full public consultation that is relevant to the development of this policy. The Department will publish a further consultation-stage impact assessment alongside this consultation.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49959/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49959/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what estimate they have made of the impact on United Kingdom gross value added and gross domestic product, and on the numbers of jobs, of the introduction of standardised tobacco packaging.","false","Biography information for Lord Palmer",,"Lord Palmer","HL6911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49960","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Department received over 668,000 responses to the <em>Consultation on standardised packaging of tobacco products </em>in 2012. A summary report of the consultation was published by the Department on 12 July 2013 and copies have already been placed in the Library.</p><p> </p><p>In 2013 the Department held a series of meetings with representatives of tobacco companies and the wider tobacco manufacturing industry to further inform the development of the impact assessment for standardised packaging of tobacco products.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will hold a final, short consultation on standardised packaging of tobacco products. In this consultation Ministers will ask, in particular, for views on anything new since the last full public consultation that is relevant to the development of this policy.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49960/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49960/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what representations they have received from organisations opposed to standardised tobacco packaging.","false","Biography information for Lord Palmer",,"Lord Palmer","HL6912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49961","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Government continues carefully to consider all issues relevant to the introduction of standardised packaging of tobacco products.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will be holding a final, short consultation including draft regulations in which Ministers will ask, in particular, for views on anything new since the last full public consultation that is relevant to the development of this policy.</p><p> </p><p>A further, developed consultation stage Impact Assessment (IA) will be published alongside the upcoming public consultation. Her Majesty's Revenue and Customs has contributed to the revised IA.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Health will continue to work with other government departments on the development of proposals for standardised packaging of tobacco products.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe","HL6914 ; HL6941","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49961/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49961/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they will place in the Library of the House all risk assessments undertaken by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills into standardised tobacco packaging.","false","Biography information for Lord Palmer",,"Lord Palmer","HL6913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49962","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Government continues carefully to consider all issues relevant to the introduction of standardised packaging of tobacco products.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will be holding a final, short consultation including draft regulations in which Ministers will ask, in particular, for views on anything new since the last full public consultation that is relevant to the development of this policy.</p><p> </p><p>A further, developed consultation stage Impact Assessment (IA) will be published alongside the upcoming public consultation. Her Majesty's Revenue and Customs has contributed to the revised IA.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Health will continue to work with other government departments on the development of proposals for standardised packaging of tobacco products.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe","HL6913 ; HL6941","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49962/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49962/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49962/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they will place in the Library of the House all risk assessments undertaken by HM Treasury into standardised tobacco packaging.","false","Biography information for Lord Palmer",,"Lord Palmer","HL6914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49963","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The 1967 Abortion Act requires that two doctors certify in good faith that there are lawful grounds for an abortion, based on an understanding of the facts of a woman's case. Any change to this requirement would require a change in the Abortion Act and this is a matter for Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>The Department will be issuing guidance shortly to all those involved in abortion care about compliance with the Abortion Act.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49963/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49963/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49963/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they intend to issue guidance to doctors regarding the permissibility of granting an abortion by means of amending form HSA1 issued under the Abortion Regulations 1991 as governed by section 1 of the Abortion Act 1967; and, if not, why not.","false","Biography information for Lord Patten",,"Lord Patten","HL6915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49964","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-13","<p>The Connecting Devon and Somerset project is scheduled to deliver superfast availability to 268,494 premises by March 2016. It is currently on track to reach this target and will have delivered to 70,000 premises by the end of July 2014, despite some delays caused by flooding.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49964/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49964/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their assessment of the reasons for the delay in implementing the Connecting Devon and Somerset Programme announced in 2013 that aims to ensure that 90 per cent of premises have access to fibre optic broadband by the end of 2016, and of the effect of that delay on business competitiveness within the South Somerset area.","false","Biography information for Lord Patten",,"Lord Patten","HL6916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49965","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Government has not developed a working definition of human eugenic practice.</p><p> </p><p>Article 51 of the European Union Charter of Fundamental Rights states that the instrument applies to Member States only when they are ‘implementing Union law'. This reflects the pre-Charter case law on the rights and principles that the Charter reaffirms.</p><p> </p><p>We have no set date for completion of consideration of the issues that relate to full ratification of the Council of Europe Convention on Human Rights and Biomedicine.</p>",,"Earl Howe","HL6919 ; HL6920","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49965/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49965/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 8 April (WA 206–7), what is their working definition of a human eugenic practice.","false","Biography information for Lord Patten",,"Lord Patten","HL6917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49966","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>Abortion on the grounds of gender alone is illegal.</p><p> </p><p>On 21 May 2013, the Department published analysis of birth ratios in the United Kingdom. This found that, when broken down by the mothers' country of birth including those born in China and India, birth ratios in no group are statistically different from the range that we would expect to see naturally occurring. The UK birth ratio is within normal limits; that is to say 105 male births per 100 female births. The full report can be found on the Gov.uk web site; enter ‘gender birth ratios'.</p><p> </p><p>However, the Department remains vigilant for anecdotal evidence of sex-selective abortion.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has not made an assessment of birth ratios or the incidence of sex-selective abortions in China and India.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49966/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49966/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49966/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their assessment of the incidence of sex-selective abortion in (1) China, and (2) India; and whether there is any evidence of that practice amongst those of Chinese or Indian background living in the United Kingdom.","false","Biography information for Lord Patten",,"Lord Patten","HL6918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49967","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Government has not developed a working definition of human eugenic practice.</p><p> </p><p>Article 51 of the European Union Charter of Fundamental Rights states that the instrument applies to Member States only when they are ‘implementing Union law'. This reflects the pre-Charter case law on the rights and principles that the Charter reaffirms.</p><p> </p><p>We have no set date for completion of consideration of the issues that relate to full ratification of the Council of Europe Convention on Human Rights and Biomedicine.</p>",,"Earl Howe","HL6917 ; HL6920","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49967/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49967/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49967/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 8 April (WA 206–7), why the principles set out in Article 3(2) of the European Union Charter of Fundamental Human Rights that prohibit human eugenic practices only apply to the United Kingdom when implementing European Union law.","false","Biography information for Lord Patten",,"Lord Patten","HL6919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49968","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-13","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The following table shows the number of releases on temporary licence and failures to return recorded at HMP Ford since 2008. Data on failures to return is unavailable before 2009 and centrally held data on temporary releases is unavailable for 2009 and 2010 when a new prison database system was introduced.</p><p> </p><p>Data on temporary release failures for 2013 will be published later this year:</p><p> </p><p><strong>HMP Ford: Release on temporary licence and failures to return </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Failures to return</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Temporary releases</p></td><td><p>21,145</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>24,606</p></td><td><p>33,381</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Failures on ROTL remain very rare, consistently accounting for less that one tenth of one per cent of all releases, but they are taken seriously. In March, we announced a range of measures to strengthen the existing temporary release provisions to ensure that the right balance is always struck between facilitating resettlement and protecting the public. Under our plans, there will be a more consistent, tougher approach to dealing with ROTL failures and, in the Criminal Justice and Courts Bill, we are seeking to increase the maximum penalty for failing to return from ROTL from six months' to two years' imprisonment.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49968/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49968/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49968/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners released on temporary licence from Ford Open Prison failed to return in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Nick Gibb","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb","197782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49969","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of absconds from HMP Ford during 2012/13 were the lowest on record. Abscond figures for 2013/14 are due to be published on 31 July 2014 as part of the Prison Performance Digest.</p><p> </p><p>Figures for the number of absconds, by prison, since 1995 are provided in the Prison Digest contained in the Prison and Probation Trusts Performance Statistics. This can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225234/prison-performance-digest-12-13.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225234/prison-performance-digest-12-13.xls</a></p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49969/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49969/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many absconders there were from Ford Open Prison in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Nick Gibb","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb","197783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49970","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Government has not developed a working definition of human eugenic practice.</p><p> </p><p>Article 51 of the European Union Charter of Fundamental Rights states that the instrument applies to Member States only when they are ‘implementing Union law'. This reflects the pre-Charter case law on the rights and principles that the Charter reaffirms.</p><p> </p><p>We have no set date for completion of consideration of the issues that relate to full ratification of the Council of Europe Convention on Human Rights and Biomedicine.</p>",,"Earl Howe","HL6917 ; HL6919","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49970/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49970/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 8 April (WA 206–7), by what date their consideration of the implications for devolved responsibilities will be completed to allow full ratification of the Council of Europe Convention on Human Rights and Biomedicine.","false","Biography information for Lord Patten",,"Lord Patten","HL6920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49971","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>The UN Security Council adopted the renewed Mandate of the United Nations Mission for the Referendum in Western Sahara (MINURSO) on 29 April. The new mandate does not include an extension of the mission's responsibilities to include human rights monitoring in the territory, but it does welcome Morocco's recent steps to strengthen the National Council on Human Rights (CNDH), and its continuing interaction with Special Procedures of the United Nations Human Rights Council, including that planned for 2014. It also welcomes the planned visit of the Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights (OHCHR) in 2014.</p><p>The British Government strongly encourages progress towards effective human rights monitoring in Western Sahara and the refugee camps in Tindouf. We also welcome Morocco's recent commitments to investigate complaints of human rights violations made to the National Council for Human Rights within three months, and to end military tribunal trials for civilians. We regularly raise human rights during dialogue with the parties to the dispute over the territory, and in discussions at the UN Security Council.</p>",,"Baroness Warsi",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49971/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49971/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they intend to support an extension of the remit of the United Nations Mission for the Referendum in Western Sahara to include monitoring of human rights in that country.","false","Biography information for Lord Steel of Aikwood",,"Lord Steel of Aikwood","HL6921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49972","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>The United States is an important international partner for the UK and we work closely with them on a range of issues relevant to the Overseas Territories. It is for the United States to answer questions about the specifics of their interests.</p>",,"Baroness Warsi",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49972/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49972/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49972/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government in which United Kingdom Overseas Territories the United States has an interest; and what form such interests take.","false","Biography information for Lord Luce",,"Lord Luce","HL6922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49973","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>Following the resumption of the Intergovernmental Authority on Development (IGAD)-chaired talks in Addis Ababa, a face-to-face meeting between South Sudan's President Kiir and former Vice President Riek Machar took place in Addis on 09 May. This resulted in the two leaders signing a new peace agreement, recommitting both sides to the Cessation of Hostilities Agreement (CoHA) originally signed in January this year. The new agreement also commits both parties to work towards a Transitional Government of National Unity which will oversee a new Constitution and guide the country towards elections. The agreement also reaffirms existing commitments to allow humanitarian assistance to reach affected populations on the ground.</p><p> </p><p>The Minister for Africa, my hon. Friend the Member for Boston and Skegness (Mark Simmonds), made a statement on 10 May welcoming the agreement as an important and long overdue step, and urging the immediate implementation of the peace deal.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Warsi",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49973/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49973/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49973/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what was the outcome of the most recent political talks commencing on 28 April in Addis Ababa on the situation in South Sudan; and whether plans are in hand to form an interim government to help end the conflict there.","false","Biography information for Lord Luce",,"Lord Luce","HL6923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49974","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Avon and Somerset Probation Trust, which was established on 1 April 2010, replaced the Avon and Somerset Probation Board, which had been created on 1 April 2001 following the merger of the two separate probation committees for Avon and for Somerset.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49974/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49974/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49974/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how long it took to merge the Avon and Somerset probation trusts.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","197847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49975","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>From incidents reported to the National Reporting and Learning System (NRLS) there is evidence that the prescription of opioid medicines for all conditions, including chronic pain, have led to fatal overdoses in patients in England and Wales. However, this information cannot be used to provide evidence of abuse.</p><p> </p><p>The report <em>A review of controlled drug incidents reported to the NRLS over seven years</em> (2005 to 2011) published in the Pharmaceutical Journal in 2013 provided details of the number and types of patient safety incidents involving Controlled Drugs (CDs), including opioid medicines, reported to the NRLS. In addition incidents with reported outcomes of death and severe harm were also analysed qualitatively. A copy of the report has been placed in the Library.</p><p> </p><p>There were 72,028 incidents reported to the NRLS over the seven year period. Of 10,678 incidents of reported harm there were 54 deaths, 74 incidents of severe harm and 10,550 incidents of other harm. Incidents involving overdose of CDs accounted for 89 (69.5%) of the 128 incidents reported of serious harm (combining death and severe harm).</p><p> </p><p>Unsafe use of CDs is the number one cause of serious harm from medication incidents reported to the NRLS. NHS England is working with the Care Quality Commission and has established a clinical safety group of the National Accountable Officers for Controlled Drugs Committee. This group is providing further guidance to Accountable Officers for Controlled Drugs and healthcare practitioners on safer use of controlled drugs.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49975/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49975/answer","HL6924 -  Lib Doc.pdf","HL6924 -  Lib Doc.pdf","A review of controlled Drug incidents - Report","A review of controlled Drug incidents - Report","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49975/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether there is any evidence that the prescription of opioid medication to relieve chronic pain has led to fatal overdoses in patients in the United Kingdom; and whether there is any evidence of abuse in the use of opiates by patients.","false","Biography information for Lord Luce",,"Lord Luce","HL6924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49976","Department of Health","false","2014-05-13","<p>NHS England has made £1.5 million available in 2014-15 to undertake the work required to establish a national learning disability mortality review function by the end of March 2015. NHS England is currently undertaking work to define the detail of how the review function will operate. However, NHS England is clear that the starting point will be the proposals put forward by the Confidential Inquiry into Premature Deaths of People with Learning Disabilities team and will aim to develop proposals with input from a range of partners.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","197898 ; 197899","2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49976/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49976/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49976/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proportion of the £2.7 million announced for learning disability in the recently published NHS England business plan for 2014-15 will be spent on the proposed premature mortality review function.","false","Biography information for Mr Tom Clarke","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Mr Tom Clarke","197897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49977","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-14","<p /> <p /> <p>We have made good progress towards the implementation of the Health and Work Service.</p><p> </p><p>The tendering process closes on 9 May 2014 and we will formally announce the successful supplier for England and Wales in July 2014. Implementation will begin in late 2014 and the details will be confirmed when the chosen supplier has been appointed.</p>",,"Lord Freud",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49977/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49977/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what progress they have made in the implementation of the Health and Work Service; and whether that implementation is being taken in stages.","false","Biography information for Lord Luce",,"Lord Luce","HL6925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49978","Department of Health","false","2014-05-13","<p>NHS England has made £1.5 million available in 2014-15 to undertake the work required to establish a national learning disability mortality review function by the end of March 2015. NHS England is currently undertaking work to define the detail of how the review function will operate. However, NHS England is clear that the starting point will be the proposals put forward by the Confidential Inquiry into Premature Deaths of People with Learning Disabilities team and will aim to develop proposals with input from a range of partners.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","197897 ; 197898","2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49978/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49978/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he expects the premature mortality review function for people with a learning disability, announced in the NHS England business plan 2014-15, to become fully operational; whether the data from that review will be analysed at a national level; and when he expects initial findings from that review to become available.","false","Biography information for Mr Tom Clarke","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Mr Tom Clarke","197899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49979","Department of Health","false","2014-05-13","<p>People should expect the right support to help them manage their long-term conditions, including chronic pain, and through the Mandate we have asked NHS England to make measurable progress towards making the National Health Service among the best in Europe at supporting people with ongoing health problems to live healthily and independently, with much better control over the care they receive.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England and its partners are working towards the implementation of the House of Care model, which is designed to support the delivery of person-centred, coordinated care, which enables individuals to make informed decisions which are right for them, and empower them to self-care.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England is working to produce with patients and carers a supported self-management guide for people with complex care needs and frailty by June 2014 and is developing practical tools and commissioning guidance to support the delivery of the Mandate commitment for everyone with a long term condition being offered a personalised care plan by April 2015.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49979/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49979/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to ensure that all patients with chronic pain have access to self-management resources to enable them to support themselves.","false","Biography information for Lord Luce",,"Lord Luce","HL6926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49980","Department of Health","false","2014-05-13","<p>NHS England has made £1.5 million available in 2014-15 to undertake the work required to establish a national learning disability mortality review function by the end of March 2015. NHS England is currently undertaking work to define the detail of how the review function will operate. However, NHS England is clear that the starting point will be the proposals put forward by the Confidential Inquiry into Premature Deaths of People with Learning Disabilities team and will aim to develop proposals with input from a range of partners.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","197897 ; 197899","2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49980/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49980/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-06",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether responsibility for implementing the premature mortality review function for people with a learning disability, announced in the NHS England business plan 2014-15 will sit at a national or local level; whether all local areas in England will be mandated to implement the review; and how local areas will be held accountable for implementing the review.","false","Biography information for Mr Tom Clarke","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Mr Tom Clarke","197898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49981","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>I refer the noble Lord to the answer given by the Minister of State, my Rt. Hon. Friend the Member for Faversham and Mid Kent (Mr Robertson), on 6 May 2014, Official Report, column 73W.</p>",,"Baroness Warsi",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49981/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49981/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-06",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their policy regarding the breakdown of Israeli–Palestinian talks.","false","Biography information for Lord Luce",,"Lord Luce","HL6927"
