"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49595","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>The Government intends to transform the Highways Agency into a government-owned company, as confirmed in the response to consultation published on 30<sup>th</sup> April. In accordance with TUPE principles, we expect the pay and terms of employment of all staff to remain unchanged once transferred except for the necessary technical amendments to reflect the change to company status.</p><p> </p><p>Staff management arrangements for the company following transition, including pay and reward, are still being worked through within government. We aim to establish appropriate conditions to allow the company to fulfil its functions efficiently and effectively, whilst keeping costs down for the taxpayer. This will reflect the Government's pay policy, as well as support the delivery of a substantially increased investment programme.</p><p> </p><p>There is no intention to encourage or create opportunities for legal tax reduction schemes as part of Highways Agency transformation.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","197664 ; 197665","2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49595/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49595/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether any increase in remuneration of senior managers in the Highways Agency will have to be agreed by him when the Agency is transformed into a government-owned company.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","197663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49596","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>The Government intends to transform the Highways Agency into a government-owned company, as confirmed in the response to consultation published on 30<sup>th</sup> April. In accordance with TUPE principles, we expect the pay and terms of employment of all staff to remain unchanged once transferred except for the necessary technical amendments to reflect the change to company status.</p><p> </p><p>Staff management arrangements for the company following transition, including pay and reward, are still being worked through within government. We aim to establish appropriate conditions to allow the company to fulfil its functions efficiently and effectively, whilst keeping costs down for the taxpayer. This will reflect the Government's pay policy, as well as support the delivery of a substantially increased investment programme.</p><p> </p><p>There is no intention to encourage or create opportunities for legal tax reduction schemes as part of Highways Agency transformation.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","197663 ; 197665","2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49596/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49596/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether senior managers in the Highways Agency will be able to enter into legal tax reduction schemes when the Agency is transformed into a government-owned company.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","197664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49597","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>The Government intends to transform the Highways Agency into a government-owned company, as confirmed in the response to consultation published on 30<sup>th</sup> April. In accordance with TUPE principles, we expect the pay and terms of employment of all staff to remain unchanged once transferred except for the necessary technical amendments to reflect the change to company status.</p><p> </p><p>Staff management arrangements for the company following transition, including pay and reward, are still being worked through within government. We aim to establish appropriate conditions to allow the company to fulfil its functions efficiently and effectively, whilst keeping costs down for the taxpayer. This will reflect the Government's pay policy, as well as support the delivery of a substantially increased investment programme.</p><p> </p><p>There is no intention to encourage or create opportunities for legal tax reduction schemes as part of Highways Agency transformation.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","197663 ; 197664","2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49597/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49597/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Highways Agency will be subject to the Government's public sector pay policy when it is transformed into a government-owned company.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","197665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49598","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-08","<p>Special provisions apply to Government Departments and health authorities that enable them to recover VAT incurred on certain of their non-business activities. These are set out in section 41(3) of the VAT Act 1994.</p><p>New bodies are not automatically covered by the above provisions, but the Treasury keeps all taxes under review.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49598/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49598/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Highways Agency will be able to recover VAT in the same way as it can as an executive agency of his Department when it is transformed into a government-owned company.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","197666"
