l Poulter","197686 ; 197690","2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49618/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49618/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure that redundancies and constraints on spending in NHS England do not adversely affect the quality of services provided.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","197681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49619","Department for Education","false","2014-05-12","<p>Local Safeguarding Children Boards (LSCBs) are funded by contributions from the local authority, Primary Care Trust, police and other agencies, with the largest contribution coming from the local authority. It is important that agencies work together to agree budgets locally and prioritise spending in response to local needs and issues.</p><p>The Department for Education provided the Association of Independent LSCB Chairs with funding of £240,000 between September 2012 and March 2014 to support the leadership of LSCBs in ensuring the effectiveness of local safeguarding arrangements. We will provide them with a further £130,000 in this financial year as they move towards self-sustainability.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49619/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49619/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what funding his Department provides for Local Safeguarding Children Boards.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","197635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49620","Home Office","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>Local Safeguarding Children Boards (LSCBs) play a crucial role in multi agency <br>child protection arrangements. Decisions by individual police forces to financially <br>contribute to LSCBs are an operational matter and the Department does not hold <br>this information.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49620/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49620/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what financial contributions police services across England and Wales make to Local Safeguarding Children Boards.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","197636"
