"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49627","Attorney General","false","2014-05-08","<p>I have had no specific discussions with the Crown Prosecution Service about pre-signing of abortion forms by the 67 doctors.</p>","Beaconsfield","Mr Dominic Grieve",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49627/answer","Biography information for Mr Dominic Grieve","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49627/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what discussions he has had with the Crown Prosecution Service about the 67 doctors who are accused of pre-signing abortion referral (HSA1) certificates.","false","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","197700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49628","Department of Health","false","2014-05-08","<p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC) previously investigated the prevalence of the pre-signing of abortion (HSA1) certificates due to a specific request in 2012. The CQC has put in place information for its own staff to help identify if pre-signing or other instances of non-compliance are taking place to make sure that such cases would be picked up during inspections. This is in line with how the CQC would handle any information of concern identified during an inspection.</p><p> </p><p>If a CQC inspection identifies pre-signing or other instances of non-compliance with the Health and Social Care Act and Regulations then appropriate regulatory action will be taken. This includes reporting any concerns in relation to termination of pregnancy practice to the Department. The Department has not received any notification of pre-signing of abortion certificates from the CQC since these inspections.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49628/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49628/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the prevalence of the pre-signing of abortion (HSA1) certificates since the conclusion of the Care Quality Commission's 2012 investigations into abortion clinics.","false","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","197701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49629","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>DFID adheres to Development Co-Operation Directorate (OACD-DAC) expenditure coding requirements to allow comparison across donor spending towards attainment of the Millennium Development Goal targets. This measures against coding titles as have been internationally agreed. Only coding titles as have been internationally agreed can be individually disaggregated by DFID systems.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49629/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49629/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-02",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 10 April 2014, Official Report, column 380W, on developing countries: family planning, how much of her Department's budget has been allocated to achieving the outcomes in her Department's policy paper Safe and Unsafe Abortion in each of the last two years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","197698"
